SIMPLE: defensor
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Defensor
<hw>De*fen"sor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. See
<er>Defenser</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A defender.</def>
<rj><au>Fabyan.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>A defender or an advocate in court;
a guardian or protector.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Eccl.)</fld> <def>The patron of a church; an
officer having charge of the temporal affairs of a church.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Defensory</ent>⟦br⟧
